5:
I never expected to see you studying
abroad at the academy, let alone
becoming its student council
president.
8:
I didn't expect to run into you either.
You even beat me to befriending the
Shibuyans...
17:
Oh, sorry, I should probably explain.
Mr. Liam was my private tutor when I
was younger.
20:
...At least for a little while. He was
fired almost immediately for being
too candid with his speech.
27:
Still... Even though it was only for a
short time, his lessons stayed with
me. I appreciated how he didn't let
himself be bound by tradition.
31:
Now that's surprising to hear. You
were so prideful and stubborn when
you were young. I didn't think you
were listening.
36:
Excuse me? I compliment you, and
that's what you follow up with? This
is exactly why you got fired so fast!
40:
Ahem. Moving on, I believe I have a
grasp of your situation. Allow me to
assist.
44:
...Right. I'm sure you're offering out of
the kindness of your heart, and not
because you want to peek at all the
academy's facilities and research.
47:
Why can't it be both? I genuinely
wish to help and satisfy my curiosity
at the same time. It'sâ€”
51:
Optimal for both parties, so why
would we say no, right?
58:
We'll put you to work and get all
these messes sorted in a flash!
64:
Seriously! Why is it just one thing
after another? It's like we're cursed
or something!
68:
...I wonder if it's because of all the
people who awakened to their
powers.
72: I can't deny that is a possibility.
76:
Your city was preserved in the Void
through essentially a shared illusion,
manifested by your powers. Such an
ability goes beyond what we know
and understand about magic.
78:
The basis of magic itself has been
shaken by the revelation. I'm sure
the people of Voluntas are also
struggling to come to terms with it...
80: However, more than any of that...
84:
The cause is, most likely, the
difficulty of adjusting to another
culture.
88:
As far as I can tell, he fainted from
looking at the monster display, but
didn't hit his head.
92:
I guess these things are pretty scary
if you're not used to seeing them.
96:
Research on the serpents? How
fascinating...
101:
Those dragons have been causing
quite the stir with their attempts to
reach the Kaleidoscope.
103:
Which is why the academy's looking
into methods of dealing with them.
This display is only a portion of the
research.
117:
Thanks for all your hard work. I think
that's about every problem solved
for now.
119:
We should return to the meeting
room and check in on Dia and the
others.
124:
Oh! We should grab some snacks
before we head back, then!
127:
Like, the pres is actually putting in
effort. Guess she really wants to
stand out.
129:
What a joke. Isn't she from the
Farlands? What's she doing here at
Voluntas anyway?
132:
And who invited those Shibuya
weirdos? Theyâ€”
135:
I'm sorry about that. Those students
were out of line.
139:
You've got nothing to apologize for!
They're the ones who should be
sorry! They've got no right to judge
anyoneâ€”especially not you!
144:
I understand why they might feel
the way they do, though.
148:
I'm actually from one of the
Farlands' Nine Houses. A Sextan, in
fact. Surprise!
151:
That's part of why I became the
student council president. There are
politics to consider.
155:
In other words, I was pretty much
given the seat! It's no wonder some
of the students don't view me as
their real president.
162:
What's wrong with being given your
position, as long as you properly
perform your duties? I wouldn't pay
the other students any mind.
167:
Liam, there's probably a better way
to phrase that...
172:
You want to know what's wrong? I'll
tell you! I never wanted to be
president in the first place!
176:
I don't have time for research with
all these responsibilities on my
plate... Otherwise, I would've made
my precious child even more
magnificent than she already is...
180: Did you craft a magical servant?
184:
Oh, did I forget to tell you? My
display for the festival is her. Over
there.
189:
No way, that huge mecha's yours?! I
mean, the face is kinda jank, but,
like, dang!
194:
You take that back! I will not accept
any slander about my baby!
197:
But well... I guess she could use
some work. As it is, she's less golem
and more pretty statue with a sound
relay system installed.
201:
I-I didn't mean anything bad by it! I
seriously think it's cool! 
The face gives it some flavor.
Wait. Did you say it's a golem?
204:
It would be a huge hassle to deal
with if it ever went out of control.
208:
I-it won't! It can't! I didn't have time
to install an autonomic system!
211:
Though I get the concern. The
academy does have a history of
golems running wild...
215:
We are getting better at our control
mechanisms! I promise we've been

218:
Somebody help! The cleaning
golems are rebelling!
225: E-er, I guess that's our cue! Let's go!
